Press Releases.Title: 68 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 20 August 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 68 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore, the vast majority of whom are Work Permit holders currently under quarantine. Based on our investigations so far, there are no cases in the community.

2.   There are 2 imported cases, both of whom had been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore.

3.    We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight.


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
20 AUGUST 2020
